com.github.gwtd3.api.arrays

Interface NumericForEachCallback


  • public interface NumericForEachCallback
    Same as ForEachCallback but ensure the result is treated as a numeric double.
    Author:
    Anthony Schiochet

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      double forEach(Object thisArg, Value element, int index, Array<?> array)

    • Method Detail

      • forEach

        double forEach(Object thisArg,
             Value element,
             int index,
             Array<?> array)
        Executed for each element of the array with an assigned value.

        If a thisArg parameter is provided to Array#forEach(NumericForEachCallback, Object), it will be used as the thisArg parameter for each callback invocation.

        If thisArg is undefined or null, the this value within the function depends on whether the function is in strict mode or not (passed value if in strict mode, global object if in non-strict mode).

        Parameters:
        thisArg -
        element -
        index -
        array -
        See Also:
        https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/forEach
